with their bare hands.


32
0:1:54,887 --> 0:1:56,807
<i>That can't be true,</i>


33
0:1:56,807 --> 0:1:59,887
- Look for hypertrophic cardiomyopathy.
- What happened?


34
0:1:59,887 --> 0:2:3,767
- Pre-syncope.
- So, this board member almost fainted?


35
0:2:3,767 --> 0:2:6,647
- l'll fire up the paddles.
- Dr Weisenheimer's back.


36
0:2:6,647 --> 0:2:8,807
- How was your ski trip?
- l'm confused.


37
0:2:8,807 --> 0:2:10,567
- You annoy me.
- Now l get it.


38
0:2:10,567 --> 0:2:14,287
But you have a charm
everyone else here seems to respond to.


39
0:2:14,287 --> 0:2:16,87
Use it. OK, sport?


40
0:2:16,87 --> 0:2:25,327
<i>Great an 80-year-old</i>
<i>grouchy pretentious,,,</i>


41
0:2:25,327 --> 0:2:28,607
<i>,,,smokin'-hot bitty,</i>


42
0:2:28,607 --> 0:2:34,527
<i>Who do you love the most?</i>


43
0:2:34,527 --> 0:2:37,207
Sweetheart, are you getting younger?


44
0:2:37,207 --> 0:2:39,407
This is Dr Dorian.


45
0:2:39,407 --> 0:2:50,207
- He'll be looking after you.
- And who will be looking after him?


46
0:2:50,207 --> 0:2:54,287
Since your jaw is wired shut,
we'll give you lV nutrition, OK?


47
0:2:54,287 --> 0:2:56,567
Sorry. lt's like the dentist.


48
0:2:56,567 --> 0:3:0,87
They ask you questions and
you have that stuff in your mouth.


49
0:3:0,87 --> 0:3:2,847
l did it again. Dr Greenberg.


50
0:3:2,847 --> 0:3:4,687
What kind of doctor are you?


51
0:3:4,687 --> 0:3:9,367
l keep doing it. Just act it out.


52
0:3:9,367 --> 0:3:11,887
Head?


53
0:3:11,887 --> 0:3:13,967
Shrinking. A shrink!


54
0:3:13,967 --> 0:3:17,607
l can't imagine picking
psychiatry as a specialty


55
0:3:17,607 --> 0:3:19,567
after interning as a real doctor.


56
0:3:19,567 --> 0:3:22,887
That didn't come out right.
My dad. He's a doctor too.


57
0:3:22,887 --> 0:3:26,527
He says therapy is for people
with more money than problems.


58
0:3:26,527 --> 0:3:31,7
But then... my dad says a lot of things.


59
0:3:31,7 --> 0:3:34,7
- Did anyone page a nurse?
- No.


60
0:3:34,7 --> 0:3:39,807
- lt looks like his eyes are screaming.
- Please, we're talking.


61
0:3:39,807 --> 0:3:42,367
Where was l?


62
0:3:42,367 --> 0:3:45,567
- You should get dressed.
- l can't. lt's still out there.


63
0:3:45,567 --> 0:3:50,207
Don't call my mother ''it''. lt implies
you think that she's a monster.


64
0:3:50,207 --> 0:3:53,7
Get a move on,
it gets up to feed about now.


65
0:3:53,7 --> 0:3:56,167
l don't understand
why we couldn't stay at my place.


66
0:3:56,167 --> 0:3:58,247
l could've done the whole show.


67
0:3:58,247 --> 0:4:0,567
- There's a show?
- Yeah, there's a show.


68
0:4:0,567 --> 0:4:4,847
lt involves music, some dancing,
occasionally singing.


69
0:4:4,847 --> 0:4:11,527
- Can you do <i>Me And Mrs Jones?</i>
- l don't know, what's she look like?


70
0:4:11,527 --> 0:4:15,927
You wanted to spend the whole night
together. l can't leave my mother alone.


71
0:4:15,927 --> 0:4:22,807
She's frail.


72
0:4:22,807 --> 0:4:26,247
Tell her to put the cane down!


73
0:4:26,247 --> 0:4:29,807
- Tell her to put the cane down!
- lt's because l'm unmarried.


74
0:4:29,807 --> 0:4:31,927
She doesn't have to know we had sex.


75
0:4:31,927 --> 0:4:34,407
- She speaks English.
- Then why translate?


76
0:4:34,407 --> 0:4:36,327
You don't speak Spanish!


77
0:4:36,327 --> 0:4:41,87
No! No!


78
0:4:41,87 --> 0:4:42,887
Tell her to put the cane down.


79
0:4:42,887 --> 0:4:45,407
l have to be honest,
when Dr Kelso said


80
0:4:45,407 --> 0:4:48,527
board member, l was thinking
this like old, grumpy...


81
0:4:48,527 --> 0:4:50,687
That would be my father. He died.


82
0:4:50,687 --> 0:4:53,207
- l'm so sorry.
- 20 years ago.


83
0:4:53,207 --> 0:4:59,207
l would have said sorry then
but l had trouble with my Ss.


84
0:4:59,207 --> 0:5:4,967
l was five. Ss.
So... how are you feeling?


85
0:5:4,967 --> 0:5:7,567
Great, that's why l'm here. Listen, RJ.


86
0:5:7,567 --> 0:5:9,807
- JD.
- Like it matters.


87
0:5:9,807 --> 0:5:13,167
You seem like a nice, spineless, boy,
so let's be honest.


88
0:5:13,167 --> 0:5:17,407
l'm here because it was the only way to
end my mother's nagging pseudo-concern.


89
0:5:17,407 --> 0:5:19,887
- That's sweet.
- So, do your little tests.


90
0:5:19,887 --> 0:5:22,127
But first, close the blinds,


91
0:5:22,127 --> 0:5:26,407
wash off your 8th-grade-dance cologne
so we don't add nausea to my symptoms.


92
0:5:26,407 --> 0:5:30,647
l'll need lemon wedges for my sparkling
water, which you've yet to get.


93
0:5:30,647 --> 0:5:33,327
- Let me just...
- Doing things l want first.


94
0:5:33,327 --> 0:5:35,967
- Your little tests later.
- Nice to meet you.


95
0:5:35,967 --> 0:5:37,447
<i>I hate you,</i>


96
0:5:37,447 --> 0:5:40,447
Merry Christmas!
l mean, happy Halloween!


97
0:5:40,447 --> 0:5:43,927
l am so frazzled.
l did not sleep at all.


98
0:5:43,927 --> 0:5:50,887
ln fact, l haven't really slept
since l started here.


99
0:5:50,887 --> 0:5:54,807
lt's so much pressure. l can't talk
to anyone here. lt's so competitive.


100
0:5:54,807 --> 0:5:57,967
l used to be able to talk to
my mom, but now, l don't know,


101
0:5:57,967 --> 0:6:6,567
she listens, but she just never
seems to hear me, you know?


102
0:6:6,567 --> 0:6:10,247
Lonely, depressed, overwhelmed.


103
0:6:10,247 --> 0:6:15,327
And sometimes l have no idea
how l'll make it through this.


104
0:6:15,327 --> 0:6:17,807
No. l don't even like to take aspirin.


105
0:6:17,807 --> 0:6:19,527
l'd rather just...


106
0:6:19,527 --> 0:6:21,87
Oh, you!


107
0:6:21,87 --> 0:6:25,167
Dr Cox. l've been
thinking about your predicament


108
0:6:25,167 --> 0:6:27,967
and l think l have a solution:
cruise ships.


109
0:6:27,967 --> 0:6:30,887
- Right.
- Everyone'll call you Doc.


110
0:6:30,887 --> 0:6:35,167
You'll visit exotic ports.
Maybe you'll even get to meet Charo.


111
0:6:35,167 --> 0:6:37,927
Enjoy this while you can, Bobby.


112
0:6:37,927 --> 0:6:40,407
lf your evil genie
does grant your wish,


113
0:6:40,407 --> 0:6:43,567
and l disappear,
the only person you'll have left


114
0:6:43,567 --> 0:6:45,767
to contend with will be yourself.


115
0:6:45,767 --> 0:6:49,207
And when you really
get to know that person,


116
0:6:49,207 --> 0:6:51,407
dear God, you'll scream so loud,


117
0:6:51,407 --> 0:6:55,887
Satan will want to rip up the contract
you signed so he can get some sleep.


118
0:6:55,887 --> 0:6:59,167
Look at you with your stiff upper lip.


119
0:6:59,167 --> 0:7:13,847
l think l'm gonna miss that the most.


120
0:7:13,847 --> 0:7:15,927
What are you looking at?


121
0:7:15,927 --> 0:7:18,727
l just... l like your shirt.


122
0:7:18,727 --> 0:7:21,247
- What kind of shirt is that?
- A white T-shirt.


123
0:7:21,247 --> 0:7:26,887
l knew it.


124
0:7:26,887 --> 0:7:29,167
l will never sleep
at your place again.


125
0:7:29,167 --> 0:7:30,807
lt wasn't that bad.


126
0:7:30,807 --> 0:7:32,807
l am in such a good mood.


127
0:7:32,807 --> 0:7:35,207
Does she invite the priest over
every day?


128
0:7:35,207 --> 0:7:38,327
Only when she finds me in bed
with some guy. So most days.


129
0:7:38,327 --> 0:7:40,847
That's not funny.
That's not funny.


130
0:7:40,847 --> 0:7:44,327
l'm just in a much better place.
Do l look different?


131
0:7:44,327 --> 0:7:47,687
What kind of a shirt is that?
l am such an idiot.


132
0:7:47,687 --> 0:7:49,687
l'm in a better place.


133
0:7:49,687 --> 0:7:52,487
What do you say, my apartment, tonight?


134
0:7:52,487 --> 0:7:54,407
l'll think about it.


135
0:7:54,407 --> 0:7:56,287
Why doesn't anyone listen to me?


136
0:7:56,287 --> 0:7:59,127
ln a better place,
look different, feel good.


137
0:7:59,127 --> 0:8:1,567
That's what happens
when you see a shrink.


138
0:8:1,567 --> 0:8:4,607
My patient is a therapist.
l'm not seeing a shrink.


139
0:8:4,607 --> 0:8:7,407
Stop spreading around
embarrassing rumours.


140
0:8:7,407 --> 0:8:12,847
l'm just goofing around. The last thing
l want to do is upset a crazy lady.


141
0:8:12,847 --> 0:8:15,167
- T-shirt.
- ls anybody up there?


142
0:8:15,167 --> 0:8:17,567
Up there... up there... up there...


143
0:8:17,567 --> 0:8:20,647
l'm all alone down here...
here... here...


144
0:8:20,647 --> 0:8:23,327
lt's cold.


145
0:8:23,327 --> 0:8:29,7
l'm frightened.


146
0:8:29,7 --> 0:8:32,527
<i>Just keep moving, Refocus,</i>


147
0:8:32,527 --> 0:8:34,647
<i>Think about helping Dr Cox,</i>


148
0:8:34,647 --> 0:8:38,367
Ms Sullivan? Sorry. l didn't
realise you're in the bathroom.


149
0:8:38,367 --> 0:8:42,7
lt's OK, come on in.


150
0:8:42,7 --> 0:8:45,247
Come in the room, not in here.
What's the matter with you?


151
0:8:45,247 --> 0:8:47,767
Are you even a real doctor?


152
0:8:47,767 --> 0:8:52,447
l know that you're on the board, and l
have this friend. Well, he's a mentor...


153
0:8:52,447 --> 0:8:55,607
- Losing interest!
- Sorry.


154
0:8:55,607 --> 0:8:57,687
Why are you dressed?


155
0:8:57,687 --> 0:9:1,167
l'm going to a party.
l assume my tests are normal.


156
0:9:1,167 --> 0:9:5,407
But l sure hope we can go down
to the river some time and race frogs.


157
0:9:5,407 --> 0:9:6,767
<i>That's it,</i>


158
0:9:6,767 --> 0:9:10,167
Listen, you spoiled,
bossy chore of a woman.


159
0:9:10,167 --> 0:9:12,927
- What'd you say?
- <i>You're in now go for it,</i>


160
0:9:12,927 --> 0:9:15,887
l'm the doctor here.
So put your gown back on,


161
0:9:15,887 --> 0:9:19,967
