165
0:9:33,527 --> 0:9:41,847
- Take off your pants.
- Yes, ma'am.


166
0:9:41,847 --> 0:9:44,487
l know it's tough
leaving your mother at home.


167
0:9:44,487 --> 0:9:47,167
- l'm really glad you're here.
- You are?


168
0:9:47,167 --> 0:9:49,407
Yes, l am.


169
0:9:49,407 --> 0:9:53,47
And l promise l'm going
to make it worth your while.


170
0:9:53,47 --> 0:9:55,767
We've already slept together.


171
0:9:55,767 --> 0:9:58,407
You should be careful
about the build-up.


172
0:9:58,407 --> 0:10:2,407
- ls that necessary?
- Yeah.


173
0:10:2,407 --> 0:10:5,487
l got something for you.


174
0:10:5,487 --> 0:10:16,367
You want to hear it?


175
0:10:16,367 --> 0:10:18,807
Did you learn that for me?


176
0:10:18,807 --> 0:10:26,767
More.


177
0:10:26,767 --> 0:10:29,927
<i>The start of a relationship</i>
<i>is about three things,</i>


178
0:10:29,927 --> 0:10:31,727
<i>Control,</i>


179
0:10:31,727 --> 0:10:34,47
Oh, God!


180
0:10:34,47 --> 0:10:35,567
<i>Dependence,</i>


181
0:10:35,567 --> 0:10:39,7
He was released
a couple of hours ago.


182
0:10:39,7 --> 0:10:41,47
<i>And timing,</i>


183
0:10:41,47 --> 0:10:43,47
Your mother broke her leg.


184
0:10:43,47 --> 0:10:45,927
<i>Other than that</i>
<i>there aren't a lot of surprises,</i>


185
0:10:45,927 --> 0:10:47,687
Dr Cox have you met...?


186
0:10:47,687 --> 0:10:51,447
You don't have
to introduce me to my ex-wife.


187
0:10:51,447 --> 0:10:54,927
Surprise!


188
0:10:54,927 --> 0:11:0,87
You putz.


189
0:11:0,87 --> 0:11:2,607
- <i>Oh no,</i>
- Hello, Jordan.


190
0:11:2,607 --> 0:11:4,527
- <i>Oh no no,</i>
- Perry.


191
0:11:4,527 --> 0:11:7,87
- Perry?
- You never heard that.


192
0:11:7,87 --> 0:11:9,847
<i>And I don't have your ex-wife's</i>
<i>bite mark on my neck,</i>


193
0:11:9,847 --> 0:11:12,887
Don't look her in the eyes.
She'll steal your soul.


194
0:11:12,887 --> 0:11:15,167
How are things down in the underworld?


195
0:11:15,167 --> 0:11:19,367
Good. And you?
Still have a rollicking social life?


196
0:11:19,367 --> 0:11:22,527
Since l cut you loose
it's been one big party.


197
0:11:22,527 --> 0:11:28,87
Name some place, other than the
hospital, you've been in the last month.


198
0:11:28,87 --> 0:11:32,687
Five, four, three, two...


199
0:11:32,687 --> 0:11:35,167
My car!


200
0:11:35,167 --> 0:11:39,47
On the way to the... big party.


201
0:11:39,47 --> 0:11:41,127
That must have hurt.


202
0:11:41,127 --> 0:11:43,167
<i>I gotta get out of here,</i>


203
0:11:43,167 --> 0:11:46,847
<i>Anger like this has a way of being</i>
<i>passed on to whoever's closest,</i>


204
0:11:46,847 --> 0:11:50,847
Dr Cox, l know you're suspended but
you're the only one my mother trusts.


205
0:11:50,847 --> 0:11:55,727
Not now!


206
0:11:55,727 --> 0:12:1,127
This is all your fault.


207
0:12:1,127 --> 0:12:3,247
- Turk, can l talk...?
- No. You can't.


208
0:12:3,247 --> 0:12:8,407
That's why they're called
your problems.


209
0:12:8,407 --> 0:12:15,447
Sorry.


210
0:12:15,447 --> 0:12:19,7
Happy Halloween.


211
0:12:19,7 --> 0:12:22,767
That'll teach you not to spy on
people during their alone time.


212
0:12:22,767 --> 0:12:26,927
<i>When dealing with a crisis everyone</i>
<i>knows you go right to the source,</i>


213
0:12:26,927 --> 0:12:28,727
<i>God the source is pretty,</i>


214
0:12:28,727 --> 0:12:30,487
Ms Sullivan?


215
0:12:30,487 --> 0:12:32,167
Excuse me?


216
0:12:32,167 --> 0:12:34,447
l think we're way past Ms Sullivan.


217
0:12:34,447 --> 0:12:39,847
OK, Jordan...


218
0:12:39,847 --> 0:12:43,647
l don't think
we should see each other again.


219
0:12:43,647 --> 0:12:48,607
The story of my life. Any time l let
my guard down just a little, l get hurt.


220
0:12:48,607 --> 0:12:50,687
l am so sorry.


221
0:12:50,687 --> 0:12:54,127
You know how long it's been
since l connected with someone?


222
0:12:54,127 --> 0:12:57,767
lt's not fair that because of him,
l don't get to spend time...


223
0:12:57,767 --> 0:12:59,847
lt's hard to keep that going.


224
0:12:59,847 --> 0:13:6,887
See you, DJ, l got a date.
''See each other again!''


225
0:13:6,887 --> 0:13:9,367
She's gonna be OK.


226
0:13:9,367 --> 0:13:12,887
l don't know, Mom,
l'm just feeling lost.


227
0:13:12,887 --> 0:13:19,247
Everyone here is so busy,
and l guess l'm just kind of lonely.


228
0:13:19,247 --> 0:13:24,727
Could you just try to hear
what l'm saying? Just this once?


229
0:13:24,727 --> 0:13:27,567
No, l don't have short hair.


230
0:13:27,567 --> 0:13:31,567
Yes, l know short hair
gives me pig-face.


231
0:13:31,567 --> 0:13:34,47
Yeah.


232
0:13:34,47 --> 0:13:35,447
- Dr Cox!
- OK, Linus.


233
0:13:35,447 --> 0:13:39,687
You're too excited. Get your blankie,
go in a corner, and take a time-out.


234
0:13:39,687 --> 0:13:43,367
Non-displaced femoral fracture,
Carla's mom's gonna be fine.


235
0:13:43,367 --> 0:13:45,127
