- Your ex-wife.


236
0:13:45,127 --> 0:13:48,687
- She's the answer.
- Things That Ruined My Life?


237
0:13:48,687 --> 0:13:51,127
Things With Sharp Edges?


238
0:13:51,127 --> 0:13:55,127
She's on the board.
l'm sure she's a reasonable person.


239
0:13:55,127 --> 0:13:57,527
Not that l know her
or have been alone with her.


240
0:13:57,527 --> 0:13:59,87
- But if you just...
- No.


241
0:13:59,87 --> 0:14:1,247
- Ask.
- l'm going to go and do this


242
0:14:1,247 --> 0:14:4,247
as slowly as possible
so you don't misunderstand.


243
0:14:4,247 --> 0:14:7,87
No...


244
0:14:7,87 --> 0:14:10,7
<i>I wonder if he wants me to ask her,</i>


245
0:14:10,7 --> 0:14:15,167
Fine, l'll ask her.


246
0:14:15,167 --> 0:14:19,687
<i>That's a no,</i>


247
0:14:19,687 --> 0:14:22,687
- lt's always funny.
- Can't believe she's sleeping.


248
0:14:22,687 --> 0:14:24,567
She's had two Valium.


249
0:14:24,567 --> 0:14:28,207
- Why, was she in a lot of pain?
- No, she just wouldn't shut up.


250
0:14:28,207 --> 0:14:30,327
l'm sorry.


251
0:14:30,327 --> 0:14:33,527
l notice your little boyfriend's
name's not on the cast.


252
0:14:33,527 --> 0:14:36,287
Making me leave her alone like that?


253
0:14:36,287 --> 0:14:40,847
She would have gotten hurt,
whether you were there or not.


254
0:14:40,847 --> 0:14:42,927
She fell in the shower.


255
0:14:42,927 --> 0:14:46,767
So unless you have an extremely
disturbing relationship,


256
0:14:46,767 --> 0:14:50,247
- l'm afraid you're full of crap.
- l'm full of crap?


257
0:14:50,247 --> 0:14:53,407
lf you don't care about being
suspended, why are you here?


258
0:14:53,407 --> 0:14:56,447
You don't scare me
with those crazy eyes.


259
0:14:56,447 --> 0:14:58,887
She's an excuse to not take chances.


260
0:14:58,887 --> 0:15:2,487
- You're only happy when you're here.
- You're afraid to live your own life.


261
0:15:2,487 --> 0:15:5,367
Admit that losing this place
would kill you.


262
0:15:5,367 --> 0:15:13,287
- We done?
- That's all l got.


263
0:15:13,287 --> 0:15:16,367
Crazy eyes?


264
0:15:16,367 --> 0:15:18,327
Low blow.


265
0:15:18,327 --> 0:15:20,847
<i>There are other ways</i>
<i>to save Dr Cox's job,</i>


266
0:15:20,847 --> 0:15:26,367
<i>I could try talking to Dr Kelso,</i>


267
0:15:26,367 --> 0:15:30,207
<i>Cox could get plastic surgery</i>
<i>to look like Jimmie Walker,</i>


268
0:15:30,207 --> 0:15:33,247
This guy's gonna need 30mEqs of KCL.


269
0:15:33,247 --> 0:15:36,447
<i>Or I could just ask Jimmie Walker</i>
<i>to talk to Dr Kelso,</i>


270
0:15:36,447 --> 0:15:41,367
Your man Cox is the best. l know he's
got an unorthodox way of doing things,


271
0:15:41,367 --> 0:15:43,407
but all the innovators do.


272
0:15:43,407 --> 0:15:46,7
Now, everybody deserves
a second chance.


273
0:15:46,7 --> 0:15:48,687
Am l right?


274
0:15:48,687 --> 0:15:50,767
Who are you?


275
0:15:50,767 --> 0:15:56,567
<i>Or I could get back</i>
<i>to the problem at hand,</i>


276
0:15:56,567 --> 0:15:59,47
l know you're on your way
to the board meeting


277
0:15:59,47 --> 0:16:1,607
and l know
you don't really like me, but...


278
0:16:1,607 --> 0:16:3,687
l don't dislike you. l nothing you.


279
0:16:3,687 --> 0:16:7,367
Thanks, that's special.
l have to ask you a favour.


280
0:16:7,367 --> 0:16:9,847
But this is not why we slept together.


281
0:16:9,847 --> 0:16:13,247
You had nothing to do
with why we slept together.


282
0:16:13,247 --> 0:16:16,487
l think we both know
that's not completely true.


283
0:16:16,487 --> 0:16:20,407
Even though you're terrified
Dr Cox will find out,


284
0:16:20,407 --> 0:16:24,7
if l wanted you to have sex with me
in front of him, you would.


285
0:16:24,7 --> 0:16:25,967
Please don't do that.


286
0:16:25,967 --> 0:16:29,127
You remind me of him
when he was younger.


287
0:16:29,127 --> 0:16:31,207
Then see if you can dig up sympathy


288
0:16:31,207 --> 0:16:36,887
for someone who means a whole lot to me,
and probably means a little to you, too.


289
0:16:36,887 --> 0:16:39,927
- So will you help him?
- Ah, sweetie...


290
0:16:39,927 --> 0:16:42,247
No.


291
0:16:42,247 --> 0:16:45,167
- l went to therapy once.
- You did?


292
0:16:45,167 --> 0:16:49,687
Yeah. Once though,
like, back in '93 to '94.


293
0:16:49,687 --> 0:16:51,687
Then a few months in '95.


294
0:16:51,687 --> 0:16:54,687
And then l went to group,
which was a disaster.


295
0:16:54,687 --> 0:16:58,527
When l went to college it was
my first time away from home.


296
0:16:58,527 --> 0:17:1,527
Things started piling up
and l felt l was sinking.


297
0:17:1,527 --> 0:17:4,447
- Yeah.
- And no matter how embarrassing


298
0:17:4,447 --> 0:17:8,287
you think it might be, it's always
helpful to talk to someone neutral.


299
0:17:8,287 --> 0:17:11,567
For example, take a look at me.
l am now, thanks to therapy,


300
0:17:11,567 --> 0:17:14,327
in a healthy relationship
with a beautiful woman,


301
0:17:14,327 --> 0:17:20,47
who won't sleep over because
she thinks l broke her mother's leg.


302
0:17:20,47 --> 0:17:24,287
Baby!


303
0:17:24,287 --> 0:17:26,887
How long were you back there?
For a second, huh?


304
0:17:26,887 --> 0:17:29,687
- l wasn't talking about us...
- Turk.


305
0:17:29,687 --> 0:17:33,767
Mom's spending the night here,
so l will spend the night with you,


306
0:17:33,767 --> 0:17:37,887
only we have to leave right now.


307
0:17:37,887 --> 0:17:49,87
Go.


308
0:17:49,87 --> 0:17:52,367
<i>Sometimes no matter how badly</i>
<i>you want to stop something</i>


309
0:17:52,367 --> 0:17:54,687
<i>there's nothing you can do to stop it,</i>


310
0:17:54,687 --> 0:17:57,47
<i>The board of directors</i>
<i>of Sacred Heart</i>


311
0:17:57,47 --> 0:18:2,327
<i>is behind that door sipping water</i>
<i>and killing the career of Dr Cox,</i>


312
0:18:2,327 --> 0:18:5,247
Yes. l am bullet-proof.


313
0:18:5,247 --> 0:18:9,327
- <i>He's taking it well,</i>
- So, no hard feelings?


314
0:18:9,327 --> 0:18:12,407
- Careful.
- Catch you on the flip side.


315
0:18:12,407 --> 0:18:15,687
l really think
you're making a big mistake.


316
0:18:15,687 --> 0:18:19,207
- The most destructive thing about Dr...
- Yawn!


317
0:18:19,207 --> 0:18:25,47
l say yawn because when l actually yawn,
you don't get it.


318
0:18:25,47 --> 0:18:26,807
See you in hell.


319
0:18:26,807 --> 0:18:29,327
<i>I don't know why she did it</i>
<i>maybe I got to her,</i>


320
0:18:29,327 --> 0:18:31,927
<i>Maybe she knows how much</i>
<i>the hospital needs him,</i>


321
0:18:31,927 --> 0:18:35,127
<i>Maybe she remembers why</i>
<i>she cared about him in the first place,</i>


322
0:18:35,127 --> 0:18:38,887
l did it cos the thought of you
rotting here in this fluorescent tomb


323
0:18:38,887 --> 0:18:42,967
is more fun than tipping a valet
with your alimony cheque.


324
0:18:42,967 --> 0:18:47,407
Listen, pumpkin, if you're having
this much trouble getting over me,


325
0:18:47,407 --> 0:18:49,607
just go ahead and give me a call,


326
0:18:49,607 --> 0:18:52,567
and l'll toss you
a sympathy throw-down any time.


327
0:18:52,567 --> 0:19:1,607
<i>It made me realise</i>
<i>every ending leads to new complications,</i>


328
0:19:1,607 --> 0:19:6,407
<i>New problems to be dealt with,</i>


329
0:19:6,407 --> 0:19:11,127
l'm watching that.


330
0:19:11,127 --> 0:19:17,7
- <i>New issues,</i>
- Thanks, Dr Greenberg.


331
0:19:17,7 --> 0:20:1,367
See you next week.


332
0:20:1,367 --> 0:20:5,167
- She was never boring.
- What happened?


333
0:20:5,167 --> 0:20:10,207
You marry somebody like your mother
then remember you hate your mother.


334
0:20:10,207 --> 0:20:13,327
You asked her for help, didn't you?


335
0:20:13,327 --> 0:20:16,647
You don't realise how important
you are around here.


336
0:20:16,647 --> 0:20:20,407
<i>I'll always remember that as</i>
<i>the first thank-you I got from Dr Cox,</i>


337
0:20:20,407 --> 0:20:24,927
Jeez, Agnes. Does the field-hockey team
know that you're missing?


338
0:20:24,927 --> 0:20:26,367
<i>It felt good,</i>


339
0:20:26,367 --> 0:20:31,927
Although it did take
some stones to be honest.


340
0:20:31,927 --> 0:20:38,327
Stick with the truth and you can't
get hurt. Always been my philosophy.


341
0:20:38,327 --> 0:20:42,607
- You didn't sleep with her, did you?
- God, no.


342
0:20:42,607 --> 0:22:42,607
<i>Philosophy is tricky,</i>


